<section xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="virtclientrefinstallandconfig">
        <title>Installation &amp; Configuration</title>
        <para>There are two installation types to consider:</para>
        <itemizedlist mark="bullet">
          <listitem>
            <para>If you have an existing Virtuoso instance, or will install Virtuoso on a different
host, you only need to install of the 
            <link linkend="virtclientrefinstallandconfigonwin">ADO.Net Provider Client</link>
             on the Visual Studio host.</para>
          </listitem>
          <listitem>
            <para>If you have no existing Virtuoso instance, you can

            <link linkend="virtclientrefinstallandconfigvirt">install both the ADO.Net Provider Client and the Virtuoso Universal Server</link>
             on the Visual Studio host.</para>
          </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <section xml:id="virtclientrefinstallandconfigonwin">
          <title>Installation of the ADO.Net Provider Client on Windows</title>
          <para>The Virtuoso ADO.Net Provider is part of the Virtuoso Client Connectivity Kit installer,
and if the target Virtuoso Server installation  already exists on the network this is the only component
that needs to be installed.
          </para>
          <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>Download and run the Virtuoso Client Connectivity Kit installer for your target Windows OS:

</para>
              <itemizedlist mark="bullet">
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    <link xlink:href="http://download.openlinksw.com/download/login.vsp?pfam=2&amp;pform=26&amp;pcat=51&amp;prod=virtuoso-connect-psnl&amp;os=i686-generic-win-32&amp;release-dbms=5.0-virt50">Windows 98/NT/2000/XP/2003/Vista/2008 (32 Bit) (x86)
</link>
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    <link xlink:href="http://download.openlinksw.com/download/login.vsp?pfam=2&amp;pform=26&amp;pcat=51&amp;prod=virtuoso-connect-psnl&amp;os=x86_64-generic-win-64&amp;release-dbms=5.0-virt50">Windows XP/2003/Vista/2008 (64 Bit) (x86_64) 
</link>
                  </para>
                </listitem>
              </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Choose the "run" button to allow the signed "Virtuoso Client Connectivity kit" installer to start.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="ado1" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Run</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/ado1.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Choose the "Next" button to begin the installation process.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="ado3" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Installation: Next</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/ado3.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Check the "I agree with license agreement" checkbox and choose the "Next" button.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="ado4" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Installation: Agree license</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/ado4.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Choose the "Custom" option to manually select what components are installed and in which location, or choose the "Typical" or "Complete" options as recommended and skip to step 7.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="ado5" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Custom Install</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/ado5.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>If the "Custom" option what chosen, select the installation directory or leave default and choose the "Next" button to continue.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="ado6" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Installation</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/ado6.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Select which of the ADO.NET Providers are to be installed and choose "Next" to continue.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="ado7" floatstyle="1">
                <title>ADO.NET Providers</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/ado7.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>The installer is now ready to begin the installation, choose the "Install" button to commence the process.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="ado8" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Install</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/ado8.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>The installation was successfully completed.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="ado10" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Completed installation</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/ado10.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>The installation of the Provider can be verified by checking the %WINDOWS%\assembly folder and checking that the Provider(s) chosen for installation is(are) listed - "virtado3" and/or "virtado2".
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adon8_blank" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Provider</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adon8.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
          </orderedlist>
          <para>The installation of the ADO.Net Provider Client is complete.</para>
          <section xml:id="virtclientrefinstallandconfigonwinuninst">
            <title>Uninstallation</title>
            <orderedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>If you attempt to run the installer again, the following message will be displayed.
                </para>
                <figure xml:id="adon9" floatstyle="1">
                  <title>Installer message</title>
                  <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="ui/adon9.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </mediaobject>
                </figure>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>The Provider can be uninstalled from the "Control Panel" -&gt; "Programs and Features"
menu, by selecting the "Virtuoso Client Connectivity kit" from the list of installed components and clicking
the "unistall" option presented.
                </para>
                <figure xml:id="ado11" floatstyle="1">
                  <title>Uninstall</title>
                  <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="ui/ado11.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </mediaobject>
                </figure>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>Choose "Yes" to uninstall the Virtuoso ADO.Net Provider.
                </para>
                <figure xml:id="ado12" floatstyle="1">
                  <title>Uninstall</title>
                  <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="ui/ado12.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </mediaobject>
                </figure>
              </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
          </section>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="virtclientrefinstallandconfigvirt">
          <title>Installation of the ADO.Net Provider Client and Virtuoso Universal Server on Windows</title>
          <para>If both the ADO.Net Provider client and Virtuoso Server are to be installed on the same
Windows machine, then the Virtuoso Universal Server installer can be used as it includes all the Virtuoso
client and server components available in a single installer. An instance in which this particular
installation type is require would be when using the Provider to provide Entity Framework connectivity
to the remote database schema objects.</para>
          <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>Download and run the Virtuoso Universal Server installer for your target Windows OS:

</para>
              <itemizedlist mark="bullet">
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    <link xlink:href="http://download.openlinksw.com/download/login.vsp?pfam=2&amp;pform=26&amp;pcat=47&amp;prod=virtuoso-uim-unisvr-psnl&amp;os=i686-generic-win-32&amp;os2=i686-generic-win-32&amp;xpfam=virtuoso&amp;xpform=personal&amp;xpcat=unisvr&amp;xos=i686-generic-win-32&amp;xprod=virtuoso-uim-unisvr-psnl&amp;release-dbms=5.0-virt50&amp;proceed=Next+%3E">Windows 98/NT/2000/XP/2003/Vista/2008 (32 Bit) (x86)
</link>
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    <link xlink:href="http://download.openlinksw.com/download/login.vsp?pfam=2&amp;pform=26&amp;pcat=47&amp;prod=virtuoso-uim-unisvr-psnl&amp;os=x86_64-generic-win-64&amp;os2=x86_64-generic-win-64&amp;xpfam=virtuoso&amp;xpform=personal&amp;xpcat=unisvr&amp;xos=x86_64-generic-win-64&amp;xprod=virtuoso-uim-unisvr-psnl&amp;release-dbms=5.0-virt50&amp;proceed=Next+%3E">Windows XP/2003/Vista/2008 (64 Bit) (x86_64)
</link>
                  </para>
                </listitem>
              </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Choose the "run" button to allow the signed "Virtuoso Universal Server" installer to start.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow1" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Run</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow1.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Choose the "Next" button to begin the installation process.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow3" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Next</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow3.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Check the "I agree with license agreement" checkbox and choose the "Next" button.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow4" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Agree license</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow4.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Choose the "Custom" option to manually select what components are installed and in which location, or choose the "Typical" or "Complete" options as recommended and skip to step 7.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow5" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Custom option</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow5.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>If the "Custom" option what chosen, select the installation directory or leave default and choose the "Next" button to continue.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow6" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Installation directory</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow6.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Select which of the ADO.NET Providers are to be installed and choose "Next" to continue.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow8" floatstyle="1">
                <title>ADO.NET Providers</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow8.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>The installer is now ready to begin the installation, choose the "Install" button to commence the process.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow9" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Begin installation</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow9.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>The installation was successfully completed.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow11" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Installation completed</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow11.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Post installation the Virtuoso Server can be started by running the "Virtuoso Service Manager" which gets added to the Windows "Icons Tray" in the status bar.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow12" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Post installation</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow12.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Double click on the  "Virtuoso Service Manager" icon in the "Icons Tray" to load the application, select the "OpenLink Virtuoso Server" instance and press the "Start" button to run the Service.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow13" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Virtuoso Service Manager</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow13.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Once the Virtuoso service has successfully started, it is *recommended* that the default "dba" and "dav" passwords be changed to secure values by loading the URL "http://example.com/install" in a Web Browser which loads the following page for making these changes.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow15" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Defaults</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow15.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>The Virtuoso Server is now available for use.
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adow16" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Virtuoso Server</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adow16.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>The installation of the ADO.Net Provider can be verified by checking the %WINDOWS%\assembly folder and checking that the Provider(s) chosen for installation is(are) listed  -  "virtado3" and/or "virtado2".
              </para>
              <figure xml:id="adon8" floatstyle="1">
                <title>Installation verification</title>
                <mediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ui/adon8.png"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
              </figure>
            </listitem>
          </orderedlist>
          <para>The installation of the ADO.Net Provider Client and Virtuoso Universal Server is complete.</para>
          <section xml:id="virtclientrefinstallandconfigvirtuninst">
            <title>Uninstallation</title>
            <orderedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>If you attempt to run the installer again, the following message will be displayed.
                </para>
                <figure xml:id="adon9_01" floatstyle="1">
                  <title>Installer message</title>
                  <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="ui/adon9.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </mediaobject>
                </figure>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>The Provider can be uninstalled from the "Control Panel" -&gt; "Programs and Features" menu, by selecting the "Virtuoso Client Connectivity kit" from the list of installed components and clicking the "unistall" option presented.
                </para>
                <figure xml:id="ado11_01" floatstyle="1">
                  <title>Uninstall</title>
                  <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="ui/ado11.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </mediaobject>
                </figure>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>Choose "Yes" to uninstall the Virtuoso ADO.Net Provider.
                </para>
                <figure xml:id="ado13" floatstyle="1">
                  <title>Uninstall</title>
                  <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="ui/ado13.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </mediaobject>
                </figure>
              </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
          </section>
        </section>
      </section>
